<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Responsive Webpage</title>

    <!-- Font Awesome Icons -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.0.0/css/all.min.css">

    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
        }

        header {
            background: #333;
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        nav {
            background: #555;
            padding: 10px;
            text-align: center;
        }

        nav a {
            color: white;
            margin: 10px;
            text-decoration: none;
        }

        .content {
            column-count: 3;
            column-gap: 20px;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        .box {
            background: lightblue;
            padding: 15px;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
            display: inline-block;
            width: 100%;
        }

        .icon-section {
            text-align: center;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        .icon {
            font-size: 30px;
            margin: 10px;
            color: darkblue;
        }

        .transform {
            width: 150px;
            height: 150px;
            background: orange;
            margin: 20px auto;
            transition: 0.5s;
        }

        .transform:hover {
            transform: rotate(45deg) scale(1.2);
        }

        .animate {
            width: 100px;
            height: 100px;
            background: red;
            position: relative;
            animation: move 4s infinite;
            margin: 20px auto;
        }

        @keyframes move {
            0% { left: 0; }
            50% { left: 200px; }
            100% { left: 0; }
        }

        footer {
            background: #333;
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 10px;
        }

        /* Responsive */
        @media screen and (max-width: 768px) {
            .content {
                column-count: 1;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>

<header>
    <h1>My Responsive Webpage</h1>
    <p>Using CSS3 Features</p>
</header>

<nav>
    <a href="#">Home</a>
    <a href="#">About</a>
    <a href="#">Services</a>
    <a href="#">Contact</a>
</nav>

<div class="content">
    <div class="box">
        <h3>About Web Design</h3>
        <p>Web design involves creating visually appealing and user-friendly websites using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="box">
        <h3>Responsive Design</h3>
        <p>Responsive design ensures that web pages look good on all devices including mobiles, tablets, and desktops.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="box">
        <h3>CSS3 Features</h3>
        <p>CSS3 provides advanced features like animations, transformations, gradients, and flexible layouts.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="box">
        <h3>Benefits</h3>
        <p>It improves user experience, increases accessibility, and makes websites more interactive.</p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="icon-section">
    <h2>Our Features</h2>
    <i class="fas fa-home icon"></i>
    <i class="fas fa-user icon"></i>
    <i class="fas fa-cog icon"></i>
</div>

<div class="transform"></div>

<div class="animate"></div>

<footer>
    <p>© 2026 Web Design Lab Practical</p>
</footer>

</body>
</html>
